      about
      ==================================================
    
    section#intro.s-about
      .row.section-header(data-aos='fade-up').ind2
        .col-full
          h3.subhead About Pollux
          h1.display-1
            | Pollux is an artificially engineered maid, a community-driven assistant, one of its kind.
      // end section-header
      .row(data-aos='fade-up').ind2
        .col-full
          p.lead
            | Pollux is a web-idol with some bits of utility. All her aspects were designed in a way people can feel her as part of the community instead of just yet another tool. With a strong visual presence and bold personality injected in <i>her</i> wordings, Pollux manages to captivate users better and make them feel more comfortable around. Pollux is here to replace boring impersonal bots and enhance the social aspect of your community.
      // end about-desc
      .row
        .about-process.process.block-1-2.block-tab-full
          .process__vline-left
          .process__vline-right
          .col-block.process__col(data-item='1', data-aos='fade-right', data-aos-delay='100')
            .process__text
              h4 No boring passive speech
              p
                | In general, bots are boring. They speak in a dull, overly formal, and sound like call-center attendants.
                | Those that try to break the ice on that either tend to look unpolished due to overly colloquial wording, or just a reflex of the developer themself.
                | Pollux's wordings are constantly being improved to give the impression of a unique personality, which makes her less boring, and more lovable.
                | Some of Pollux's unusual quotes and responses are often commented around, a little trick to hook some random conversation.
                
          .col-block.process__col(data-item='2', data-aos='fade-left', data-aos-delay='200')
            .process__text
              h4 Balance between usability and utility
              p
                | Bot developers are... well... programmers. They can code very well and do things that work, pragmatism at its finest.
                | But just like engineers, they forget completely that "it works" is not enough, people should be able to use it intuitively, and any means of interface, be it visual or textual, should feel natural and look good so eye-browsing isnt a painful task.
                | Pollux is created by a Visual/UX Designer that for some reason can code. This puts Pollux in the sweetspot between utility, usability and presentation.
                
          .col-block.process__col(data-item='3', data-aos='fade-right', data-aos-delay='300')
            .process__text
              h4 Eye candy up to eleven!
              p
                | In a text-based service, the easiest and fastest solution is text-based responses and "fun", that's also the most boring.
                | Pollux has the most visually appealing minigames, profiles, cosmetics, and even the website!
                | Even if Pollux does something identical to someone else, she will probably do it in a fancier and eye-pleasing way, so why use boring ascii-based stuff when you can get exciting visuals too?
                
          .col-block.process__col(data-item='4', data-aos='fade-left', data-aos-delay='400')
            .process__text
              h4 A healthy community of its own
              p
                | Pollux draws in too much love, so our "support" server is usually bustling with friendly people.                
                | We also have some in-house mini-events and giveaways to our fellow Polluxlings, so if you're a wanderer, consider joining for a stay at Pollux's Mansion~.
                | Pollux's community is intertwined with our <a href="/partners">partnership network</a>, everyone helping each other in keeping their communities neat and tidy.
                
        // end process
      // end about-stats
    // end s-about
