    section#quickie.s-contact
      .row.section-header(data-aos='fade-up')
        .col-full
          h3.subhead.subhead--light Newbies Guide
          h1.display-1.display-1--light
            | How to Pollux 101
      .row(data-aos='fade-up')
        .col-full
          p.lead
            | Pollux can be potentially complex depending on your needs. So here's a really compact intro to get started with Pollux:

      .row
        p.lead: i I want Pollux for
        .col-five.tab-full.contact-secondary(data-aos='fade-up')
          h3.subhead.subhead--light Softmod and User Management 
          p.lead
            | Moderation is not Pollux's focus, but she provides some features on that.
          ul
            li 
              span Use 
              code p!modrole [@Role]
              span to assign a moderation/administrative role. These users can edit server settings in the <a href=/dashboard>Dashboard</a>
            li 
              span Use 
              code p!muterole [@Role]
              span to assign a role for muted users. These users cannot type in any channels.
            li 
              span Automatic roles added to users in certain levels can be set up only in the Dashboard. Insert the role, and the level. 0 to add it upon joining.
            li
              span Self-assignable roles can be set in the Dashboard, and via Discord using 
              code p!autorole add [@Role Name] ["shorthand"]
              span where "shorthand" (quotes required), are something other than the rolename to be used to aquire the role using
              code p!roleme shorthand
              span , or 
              code p!roleme Role Name
            li 
              span Disable commands and features with
              code p!disable [command]
            
            
